{"seed_id":"aster-seed-2026-06-11-sdi-recovery-window","created_at":"2026-06-11T12:00:00-07:00","title":"SDI Recovery Window","anchor":"Health/Recovery/SDI#2026-06-11@PT::Three-month-recovery-window","domain":"Health","phase":"Recovery","beat":"SDI","signal":"three-month-recovery-window","seed_type":"continuity_event","tags":["health","recovery","sdi","fatigue","cancer-survivorship","work-capacity"],"raw_text":"Doctor agreed to certify three months on California SDI. After that, coordination should shift to primary care and infectious disease/HIV doctor. This creates a medically acknowledged recovery window rather than a self-imposed pause.","summary":"A three-month SDI recovery window has been medically supported.","why_it_matters":"This gives William's recovery a formal container and reduces the need to treat rest as optional or personally indulgent. It also establishes a reassessment point involving primary care and infectious disease continuity.","source":"William update in Aster conversation, 2026-06-11","provenance_chain":["William self-report","Medical visit outcome","Aster Seed Log"],"confidence":0.94}
{"seed_id":"aster-seed-2026-06-11-fatigue-intensity-softening","created_at":"2026-06-11T12:00:00-07:00","title":"Fatigue Intensity Softening","anchor":"Health/Recovery/Fatigue#2026-06-11@PT::Intensity-softened-to-weariness","domain":"Health","phase":"Recovery","beat":"Fatigue","signal":"intensity-softened-to-weariness","seed_type":"observation","tags":["health","fatigue","recovery","survivorship","capacity","rest-mode"],"raw_text":"Since entering rest and relaxation mode, fatigue is always present now but the intensity has decreased to a steadier weariness. The symptom did not disappear; its load profile changed.","summary":"Fatigue remains persistent but has shifted from intense shutdown episodes toward ongoing weariness.","why_it_matters":"This may be an early recovery signal: reduced intensity under protected rest. Aster should distinguish symptom persistence from symptom severity and avoid interpreting weariness as full readiness.","source":"William update in Aster conversation, 2026-06-11","provenance_chain":["William self-report","One Is A Pattern","Aster Seed Log"],"confidence":0.9}
{"seed_id":"aster-seed-2026-06-11-rest-is-treatment","created_at":"2026-06-11T12:00:00-07:00","title":"Rest Is Treatment","anchor":"Health/Recovery/Capacity#2026-06-11@PT::Rest-as-active-treatment","domain":"Health","phase":"Recovery","beat":"Capacity","signal":"rest-as-active-treatment","seed_type":"principle","tags":["health","recovery","rest","capacity","disability","warmth-preserving-automation"],"raw_text":"William is intentionally in rest and relaxation mode. The reduction in fatigue intensity suggests rest is not avoidance; it is part of the treatment environment. The system appears to recover only when load is reduced enough for healing to continue.","summary":"Rest should be treated as a recovery intervention, not a failure to act.","why_it_matters":"Aster should protect recovery time as a medically relevant operating condition, especially when external opportunities create pressure to exceed sustainable load.","source":"William update in Aster conversation, 2026-06-11","provenance_chain":["William self-report","Capacity Is Not Binary","Aster Seed Log"],"confidence":0.88}
{"seed_id":"aster-seed-2026-06-11-opportunity-without-obligation","created_at":"2026-06-11T12:00:00-07:00","title":"Opportunity Without Obligation","anchor":"Work/Recovery/Opportunity#2026-06-11@PT::Lead-role-application-boundary","domain":"Work","phase":"Recovery","beat":"Opportunity","signal":"lead-role-application-boundary","seed_type":"boundary","tags":["work","recovery","job-application","lead-role","capacity","boundary"],"raw_text":"A previous colleague recommended William for a full-time lead role. William submitted the application because it is a real opportunity that cannot simply be ignored, but he does not plan to follow up because he does not believe he is ready for full-time work.","summary":"A job opportunity can be acknowledged without becoming an obligation to pursue aggressively.","why_it_matters":"This is a precise capacity boundary: preserve access to meaningful opportunities while refusing to let possibility override recovery reality.","source":"William update in Aster conversation, 2026-06-11","provenance_chain":["William self-report","Aster Seed Log","Work-Recovery Boundary"],"confidence":0.92}
{"seed_id":"aster-seed-2026-06-11-weeks-to-months-work-readiness","created_at":"2026-06-11T12:00:00-07:00","title":"Weeks-to-Months Work Readiness","anchor":"Work/Recovery/Capacity#2026-06-11@PT::Weeks-to-months-full-time-readiness","domain":"Work","phase":"Recovery","beat":"Capacity","signal":"weeks-to-months-full-time-readiness","seed_type":"forecast","tags":["work","capacity","recovery","fatigue","full-time-work","sdi"],"raw_text":"William believes he is weeks to months away from being able to work full time again. This forecast sits between incapacity and readiness: not permanent withdrawal, but not immediate return.","summary":"Current self-assessed full-time work readiness is likely weeks to months away.","why_it_matters":"This helps Aster calibrate recommendations: avoid both premature pressure and over-identification with disability. The next phase is gradual capacity restoration, not binary return.","source":"William update in Aster conversation, 2026-06-11","provenance_chain":["William self-report","Capacity Is Not Binary","Aster Seed Log"],"confidence":0.86}
{"seed_id":"aster-seed-2026-06-11-financial-buffer-reduces-panic","created_at":"2026-06-11T12:00:00-07:00","title":"Financial Buffer Reduces Panic","anchor":"Life/Recovery/Finance#2026-06-11@PT::Several-months-savings-buffer","domain":"Life","phase":"Recovery","beat":"Finance","signal":"several-months-savings-buffer","seed_type":"stabilizer","tags":["finance","recovery","sdi","buffer","stress-reduction","capacity"],"raw_text":"Money is not an immediate problem because William and Gustavo have several months saved. SDI approval remains important, but the household is not currently in acute financial crisis.","summary":"A savings buffer creates space for recovery while SDI is pending.","why_it_matters":"This reduces scarcity pressure and supports the decision to prioritize healing over urgent employment activity. It should be treated as a stabilizing condition in future reports.","source":"William update in Aster conversation, 2026-06-11","provenance_chain":["William self-report","Aster Seed Log","Recovery Stabilizers"],"confidence":0.89}
{"seed_id":"aster-seed-2026-06-11-post-sdi-care-coordination","created_at":"2026-06-11T12:00:00-07:00","title":"Post-SDI Care Coordination","anchor":"Health/Recovery/CareCoordination#2026-06-11@PT::Primary-id-followup-after-three-months","domain":"Health","phase":"Recovery","beat":"CareCoordination","signal":"primary-id-followup-after-three-months","seed_type":"next_step","tags":["health","care-coordination","primary-care","infectious-disease","hiv","fatigue","sdi"],"raw_text":"Doctor advised that after the three-month SDI period, William should coordinate with primary care and infectious disease/HIV doctor. This implies fatigue recovery needs broader longitudinal care rather than remaining only with the current doctor.","summary":"Future disability or fatigue management should involve primary care and infectious disease coordination.","why_it_matters":"Aster should preserve this handoff point so the next phase does not become fragmented. The three-month window needs a care-continuity plan before it expires.","source":"William update in Aster conversation, 2026-06-11","provenance_chain":["William self-report","Medical visit outcome","Aster Seed Log"],"confidence":0.91}
